---
import BaseHead from '../components/BaseHead.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
---

<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <BaseHead
      title="About — LongevityStack"
      description="Bernardo Paranhos is a Production Engineering student at UTFPR applying systems thinking to human longevity research."
    />
  </head>
  <body>
    <Header />
    <main>

      <div class="about-header">
        <div class="evidence-tag">Systems & Longevity Researcher</div>
        <h1>About the author</h1>
      </div>

      <div class="about-grid">
        <div class="author-card">
          <div class="avatar">BP</div>
          <div class="author-info">
            <div class="author-name">Bernardo Paranhos</div>
            <div class="author-title">Production Engineering · UTFPR, Brazil</div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="prose">

          <h2>Who I am</h2>
          <p>
            I'm a Production Engineering student at the Federal University of Technology — Paraná (UTFPR), Brazil. My academic background is in industrial systems optimization: process flow, bottleneck analysis, quality control, and operational efficiency.
          </p>
          <p>
            LongevityStack is where I apply that same systems-thinking framework to a different kind of system — the human body. Specifically, to the three variables that most predictably determine long-term cognitive performance and healthspan: sleep quality, evidence-based supplementation, and neurological resilience.
          </p>

          <h2>Why I built this</h2>
          <p>
            The biohacking and longevity space is flooded with content optimized for engagement, not accuracy. Influencers recommend supplements based on affiliate commissions. Wellness brands publish studies they funded themselves. Most "evidence-based" articles cite one paper and call it settled science.
          </p>
          <p>
            As someone trained to identify failure modes in complex systems, this bothered me. I built LongevityStack to do what most health sites don't: show the actual evidence, acknowledge its limitations, and give a practical recommendation anyway — clearly labeled as such.
          </p>

          <h2>My methodology</h2>
          <p>
            Every article on this site follows the same process:
          </p>
          <ul>
            <li>Primary sources only — PubMed, NIH, peer-reviewed journals</li>
            <li>Sample size and funding source always disclosed</li>
            <li>Conflicting evidence presented, not hidden</li>
            <li>Personal opinion clearly separated from clinical data</li>
            <li>Affiliate links disclosed inline, never disguised as recommendations</li>
          </ul>

          <h2>Academic background</h2>
          <ul>
            <li><strong>Degree:</strong> B.Eng. Production Engineering (in progress) — UTFPR, Medianeira Campus, Brazil</li>
            <li><strong>Research focus:</strong> Educational technology and AI-assisted learning systems</li>
          </ul>

          <h2>A note on credentials</h2>
          <p>
            I am not a doctor, registered dietitian, or licensed healthcare professional. Nothing on this site constitutes medical advice. I am a systems engineer who reads clinical literature carefully and communicates it honestly.
          </p>
          <p>
            If you are making decisions about your health, consult a qualified healthcare professional. Use this site as a starting point for research, not as a replacement for medical guidance.
          </p>

          <div class="contact-box">
            <div class="contact-label">Get in touch</div>
            <p>For research collaborations, corrections, or affiliate partnerships:</p>
            <a href="mailto:beparanhosborges@gmail.com" class="contact-link">beparanhosborges@gmail.com</a>
          </div>

        </div>
      </div>

    </main>
    <Footer />
  </body>
</html>

<style>
  main {
    max-width: 720px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 0 28px 80px;
  }

  .about-header {
    padding: 48px 0 32px;
    border-bottom: 0.5px solid var(--color-border);
    margin-bottom: 40px;
  }

  .evidence-tag {
    display: inline-block;
    background: var(--color-green-light);
    color: var(--color-green);
    font-size: 10px;
    font-weight: 600;
    padding: 4px 12px;
    border-radius: 20px;
    margin-bottom: 14px;
    letter-spacing: 1px;
    text-transform: uppercase;
  }

  h1 {
    font-family: 'Poppins', sans-serif;
    font-size: 32px;
    font-weight: 700;
    letter-spacing: -0.5px;
    color: var(--color-text);
  }

  .author-card {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 16px;
    background: var(--color-surface);
    border-radius: 12px;
    padding: 20px 24px;
    margin-bottom: 40px;
  }

  .avatar {
    width: 52px;
    height: 52px;
    border-radius: 50%;
    background: #C0DD97;
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    font-family: 'Poppins', sans-serif;
    font-size: 16px;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--color-green);
    flex-shrink: 0;
  }

  .author-name {
    font-family: 'Poppins', sans-serif;
    font-size: 15px;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--color-text);
    margin-bottom: 3px;
  }

  .author-title {
    font-size: 13px;
    color: var(--color-muted);
  }

  .prose h2 {
    font-family: 'Poppins', sans-serif;
    font-size: 20px;
    font-weight: 700;
    letter-spacing: -0.3px;
    margin-top: 40px;
    margin-bottom: 14px;
    color: var(--color-text);
  }

  .prose p {
    font-size: 16px;
    line-height: 1.8;
    color: var(--color-text);
    margin-bottom: 20px;
  }

  .prose ul {
    padding-left: 22px;
    margin-bottom: 20px;
  }

  .prose li {
    font-size: 16px;
    line-height: 1.75;
    color: var(--color-text);
    margin-bottom: 8px;
  }

  .prose strong {
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--color-text);
  }

  .contact-box {
    background: var(--color-surface);
    border-radius: 12px;
    padding: 24px;
    margin-top: 48px;
  }

  .contact-label {
    font-size: 10px;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 1px;
    color: var(--color-green);
    font-weight: 600;
    margin-bottom: 10px;
  }

  .contact-box p {
    font-size: 14px;
    color: var(--color-muted);
    margin-bottom: 12px;
  }

  .contact-link {
    font-size: 14px;
    color: var(--color-green);
    font-weight: 600;
    text-decoration: none;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-green-light);
  }
</style>